An engineer , who was sentenced to six months jail and 75 lashes after he was found with homemade alcohol in Saudi Arabia , has spoken of his frustration with the lack of help he received from the Australian embassy .
Grandfather Peter Mutty , from Roseberry in Sydney 's inner-west , was caught with two cartons of beer , red wine and one box of white wine in his car on August 31 last year .
The possession of alcohol is illegal in Riyadh .
Mutty was ordered to serve jail time according to the Islamic calendar and received 28 of the 75 lashes , but only received 28 .